<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="339" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
There are three specimens with flowers. This species differs well from its closely related 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Utricularia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Utricularia vulgaris" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="339" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Utricularia vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. based on the following characters: corolla with lower lip flat and spreading margins, palate without hairs (
<bibRefCitation author="Taylor, P" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="0" pageNumber="339" refId="B16" refString="Taylor, P, 1989. The genus Utricularia: a taxonomic monograph. Bulletin Additional Series XIV. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" title="The genus Utricularia: a taxonomic monograph. Bulletin Additional Series XIV." year="1989">Taylor 1989</bibRefCitation>
) and some additional characters such as, the long straight pedicels, slightly deflected from the peduncle, being three or more times longer than the bracts, free anthers not intergrown with each other, and the curved S-shaped stem (
<bibRefCitation author="Tzvelev, NN" journalOrPublisher="- Petersburg State Chemical-Pharmaceutical Academy Press, St. - Petersburg" pageId="0" pageNumber="339" refId="B17" refString="Tzvelev, NN, 2000. Manual of the vascular plants of North-West Russia (Leningrad, Pskov and Novgorod provinces). St. -Petersburg State Chemical-Pharmaceutical Academy Press, St.-Petersburg" title="Manual of the vascular plants of North-West Russia (Leningrad, Pskov and Novgorod provinces). St." year="2000">Tzvelev 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lisitsyna, LI" journalOrPublisher="KMK Scientific Press Ltd., Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="339" refId="B13" refString="Lisitsyna, LI, Papchenkov, VG, Artyemenko, VI, 2009. Flora of the Volga basin reservoirs. Determinant of the vascular plants. KMK Scientific Press Ltd., Moscow" title="Flora of the Volga basin reservoirs. Determinant of the vascular plants." year="2009">Lisitsyna et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Utricularia australis R. Br. Tobolsk distr., 400 m S of village Bajgara, lake in the floodplain of the Irtysh River, 3 Jul. 2019. Photo by author." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/458796" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3</figureCitation>
). This species is characterized by some environmental preferences. So, it was revealed that 
<taxonomicName genus="U." lsidName="U. australis" pageId="0" pageNumber="339" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">U. australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows in warm (~ 26 °C), alkaline (pH 8.3 median value) and shallow (&lt;20 cm) waters (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10452-019-09743-y" author="Ceschin, S" pageId="0" pageNumber="339" refId="B1" refString="Ceschin, S, Bellini, A, Traversetti, L, Zuccarello, V, Ellwood, NTW, 2020. https://doi.org/10.1007/s10452-019-09743-y" url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10452-019-09743-y" year="2020">Ceschin et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). The examined species grows in the European part of Russia (
<bibRefCitation author="Tzvelev, NN" journalOrPublisher="- Petersburg State Chemical-Pharmaceutical Academy Press, St. - Petersburg" pageId="0" pageNumber="339" refId="B17" refString="Tzvelev, NN, 2000. Manual of the vascular plants of North-West Russia (Leningrad, Pskov and Novgorod provinces). St. -Petersburg State Chemical-Pharmaceutical Academy Press, St.-Petersburg" title="Manual of the vascular plants of North-West Russia (Leningrad, Pskov and Novgorod provinces). St." year="2000">Tzvelev 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lisitsyna, LI" journalOrPublisher="KMK Scientific Press Ltd., Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="339" refId="B13" refString="Lisitsyna, LI, Papchenkov, VG, Artyemenko, VI, 2009. Flora of the Volga basin reservoirs. Determinant of the vascular plants. KMK Scientific Press Ltd., Moscow" title="Flora of the Volga basin reservoirs. Determinant of the vascular plants." year="2009">Lisitsyna et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
), including those specimens found in the southern regions (Astrakhan region) (
<bibRefCitation author="Kapitonova, OA" journalOrPublisher="Tatishchev, Ecology Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="339" pagination="137 - 143" refId="B6" refString="Kapitonova, OA, Sorokin, AN, Krutskikch, EV, Ivanova, AV, 2011. The materials for studying of aquatic macrophytes flora of Western Substeppe Ilmens. Bulletin of the Volga University named after V.N. Tatishchev, Ecology Series 12: 137 - 143" title="The materials for studying of aquatic macrophytes flora of Western Substeppe Ilmens. Bulletin of the Volga University named after V. N." volume="12" year="2011">Kapitonova et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
) and in the Vyatka-Kama Cis-Urals (
<bibRefCitation author="Kapitonova, OA" journalOrPublisher="Tatishchev, Ecology Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="339" refId="B7" refString="Kapitonova, OA, 2015. Synopsis of macrophyte flora of the Vyatka-Kama Cis-Urals. Phytodiversity of Eastern Europe IX (4): 4-85." title="Synopsis of macrophyte flora of the Vyatka-Kama Cis-Urals. Phytodiversity of Eastern Europe IX (4): 4 - 85." year="2015">Kapitonova 2015</bibRefCitation>
). For Western Siberia, the species was not previously recorded (
<bibRefCitation author="Lisitsyna, LI" journalOrPublisher="Science, Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="339" refId="B12" refString="Lisitsyna, LI, Papchenkov, VG, 2000. Flora of the water bodies of Russia: Determinant of the vascular plants. Science, Moscow" title="Flora of the water bodies of Russia: Determinant of the vascular plants." year="2000">Lisitsyna and Papchenkov 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Doron'kin, VM" editor="Baikov, KS" journalOrPublisher="Publishing house of the SB RAS, Novosibirsk" pageId="0" pageNumber="339" pagination="412 - 413" refId="B3" refString="Doron'kin, VM, 2012. Family of Lentibulariaceae Rich. In: Baikov, KS, Ed., Synopsis of the flora of Asian Russia: vascular plants. Publishing house of the SB RAS, Novosibirsk: 412 - 413" title="Family of Lentibulariaceae Rich." volumeTitle="Synopsis of the flora of Asian Russia: vascular plants." year="2012">Doron'kin 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
